Backup/Source of internal OSC check and release scripts
=======================================================

- Most off my scripts use colored output. You may need to source
the colorecho file before using them. It provides the required
Recho Gecho Becho Cecho Mecho Yecho shell functions.

- The scripts expect 'osc' and 'git-obs' (for gitea) commands
  to be configured to access *.opensuse.org.
- 'isc' and 'git-ibs' configured to access *.suse.de.

Traditional obs workflow (ATM TW and Code15)
------------------------
For now, to avoid inconsistencies, scripts and configs are maintained at
(git@github.com:openSUSE/zypp-ci-utils.git) in tools/ma-bin-oschk.

Team-mates should call {oscchk,oscconf,oscsubmitt} there or symlink those
scripts scripts into their $PATH. Scripts will use REALPATH(1) to find the
relevant configuration file and - in case of oscsubmitt - place the logs into
the git directory.

https://smelt.suse.de/maintained/?q=zypper may help to figure out where
we need to send the maintenance requests to, and which are distributed
by maintenance internally.


New gitea workflows
-------------------
giteastats -h
 PreReq:
  - GITEAUSER configured: "mlandres"
  - PKGS configured: libsolv libzypp zypper libzypp-testsuite-tools zypp-plugin
  - Set up 'git-obs' and 'git-ibs' commands to refer to src.suse and src.opensuse.
  - Set up 'osc' and 'isc' commands to refer OBS and IBS.
  - Create empty 'obs' and 'ibs' subdirectories. We use them for cloning the repos.
  - Login to src.suse and src.opensuse and fork the packages from pool/PKG.
   (or do it on the command line; the script will hint if a fork is missing)

Unless you use 'giteastats --commit ...' nothing bad should happen.
I.e no remote repos or PRs are touched.
